Load Packages and Data

pacman::p_load(tidyverse, rpart, rpart.plot, sparkline, visNetwork)
df <- read_csv("data/touristdata_clean.csv")

df_analysis <- df %>% 
  select(!ID) %>% 
  select(!code) %>% 
  select(!country)
anova.model <- rpart(total_cost ~ ., data = df_analysis, method = "anova", 
                     control = rpart.control(minsplit = 5, cp = 0.001, maxdepth = 10))

printcp(anova.model)

bestcp <- anova.model$cptable[which.min(anova.model$cptable[,"xerror"]),"CP"]
pruned.model <- prune(anova.model, cp = bestcp)

visTree(pruned.model, edgesFontSize = 14, nodesFontSize = 16, width = "100%")
